\layout Section

Introduction
\layout Standard

This is the User Manual for Kanzi, Cematics' intelligent web development
 tool.
 Kanzi is designed to bring the flexibility of tools that computer programmers
 have been using for years, to the world of web development.
 Kanzi's core goal is to integrate seamlessly with the web development tools
 with which you are already familiar, meaning that you can get started with
 it immediately.
\layout Standard

Kanzi is useful when you need to make changes to a large number of web pages.
 You demonstrate the changes you need made on one of the pages using your
 favourite HTML editing tool, and Kanzi will intelligently figure out what
 has changed, and how those changes are to be applied to the other pages
 you have selected.
\layout Section

Installation and Registration
\layout Subsection

Requirements
\layout Standard

Kanzi requires Java version 1.2 or greater.
 This may be downloaded from 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \url{http://java.sun.com/getjava/}

\end_inset 

, and will require just a couple of minutes to install for most users.
 Kanzi will work on any version of Windows that supports Java, including
 Windows 98, Windows 2000, Windows NT, Windows XP, and Windows ME.
\layout Subsection

Installation
\layout Standard

Double click on the Kanzi installer, which you can download from 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \url{http://cematics.com/kanzi/}

\end_inset 

, and follow the steps in the installation Wizard which appears.
 In most cases, you will not need to change any of the default settings.
\layout Subsection

Registration
\layout Standard

Initially when you install Kanzi it will be in evaluation mode, this will
 be indicated by the words 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

