\layout Section

Using Kanzi
\layout Standard

There are three basic steps to using Kanzi:
\layout Enumerate

Select the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

example
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 file, and make the changes you want to it
\layout Enumerate

Select the files to which you want those changes to be applied
\layout Enumerate

Review the changes Kanzi made, then either commit or undo them
\layout Subsection

Training Kanzi
\layout Standard

When you first start Kanzi, you will be invited to select the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

example
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 file.
 This should be one of the HTML pages that you want to modify.
 You should then use your favourite HTML editor
\begin_inset Foot
collapsed true

\layout Standard

We recommend that you use the same HTML editor that was used to create the
 files if possible.
\end_inset 

 to make the modifications to that page that you want to apply to the other
 pages, and save it.
\layout Standard

Once you have saved the file, you will be able to click on 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

Next
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 and move on to the next step.
\layout Subsection

Selecting target pages
\layout Standard

Next you must select the pages to which you would like Kanzi to apply these
 changes.
 You can select each file individually using the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

Add File(s)
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 button, or add all HTML files in a directory using the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

Add a Directory
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 button.
\layout Standard

You may now decide which of these files you would like those changes applied
 to, by clicking on them you may select and deselect them.
 Only the selected files will be modified.
\layout Standard

A much more convenient way to select the files you would like to modify
 is to use the Similarity Filter.
 You can activate it by clicking on the check box.
 You may now move the slider up and down, and files will be selected and
 deselected based on their similarity to the example file which you modified
 in the previous step.
\layout Standard

Click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

Next
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 when the files you wish to modify are highlighted.
\layout Subsection

Reviewing changes
\layout Standard

The changes will now be applied to the pages.
 This should occur quite quickly, but the time required may vary depending
 on the extent of the changes to the example page, and the number of target
 pages.
\layout Standard

You may now review the changes Kanzi has made to these pages.
 You can launch a web-browser pointing at the (modified) example page by
 clicking on 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

Review Your Documents
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

.
 You should check the target files to ensure that Kanzi has applied the
 changes correctly.
\layout Standard

If it has, you can apply the changes permenantly by clicking on 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

Finish
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

.
 You can undo the changes by clicking on 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

Undo
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

.
\layout Section

Troubleshooting
\layout Subsection

Kanzi applied my changes incorrectly
\layout Standard

Kanzi is smart, but it does have limitations and may occasionally apply
 your changes incorrectly.
 If this happens, go back, apply some of the changes, then use Kanzi again
 to apply the rest of them
\the_end
